        <detaileddescription>
<para>describes a triangle as three vertex IDs sorted in a way to quickly find same triangles irrespective of vertex order (clockwise or counterclockwise) Generated from class <computeroutput>MR::UnorientedTriangle</computeroutput>. Supported <computeroutput><ref refid="common_8h_1ac983b89bddb9b22c9b416f31399f0095" kindref="member">MR_PassBy</ref></computeroutput> modes: <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Copy</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Move</computeroutput> (and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultArgument</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_NoObject</computeroutput> if supported by the callee). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
